<user_id>108787267688956823909< /user_id>< username>
Amy Wang<//username>
<Date>1614569064011<//Date><Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
I absolutely love the coconut puddings here! This place has replaced boba milk tea in my life.

I have now tried almost all of the flavors!

Here are my favorites. Note that I personally prefer mild and lightly sweet flavors.

My top favorites are the:
- Signature Coconut Pudding - This is a refreshing light pudding that tastes like fresh coconut water with some milk (lactose free, according to Tong Sui) with possibly a little sugar added. The coconut flakes add a little bit more sweetness and a crunchy texture to go with the pudding.

- Osmanthus Sweet Rice Coconut Pudding - This pudding consists of a light jelly made from osmanthus (a small fragrant, yellow flower) with a thin layer of rice between the osmanthus jelly and the signature coconut pudding. The rice has a mild aroma of rice wine that I really enjoy

Close second favorites are:
- Double Layer Coconut Pudding - Same as the signature with a layer of jelly made from coconut water on top of the signature pudding.

- Strawberry Coconut Pudding - Also similar to the signature with a layer of strawberry flavored coconut pudding on top of the signature pudding. The strawberry flavoring is very light and natural.

- Taro and Purple Yam Coconut Pudding - This is a great flavor combination. This is a puree of taro and purple yam on top of the signature pudding. I think the puree is probably lightly sweetened. If you're lucky and you get one freshly made, then the taro and yam are still warm on top of the pudding.

- Red Bean Mochi Coconut Pudding - This is another great combination. The mochi is very soft and easy to scoop up with a spoon and it is mixed in with red bean and then put on top of the signature pudding. When I had this, it was a holiday special.

Good but not my preference:
- Matcha Coconut Pudding with Red Bean - I do love matcha flavors but I felt like matcha masked the coconut pudding flavor that I was looking for.

- Chocolate Coconut Pudding - The chocolate pudding on top is really good but I definitely felt it heavily overpowered the mild taste of the signature pudding below.

Not my preference:
- Rosewater Peach Gum Coconut Pudding - This is a signature pudding topped with an unsweetened rosewater and peach gum jelly. This pudding is probably my least favorite but I also don't really enjoy rose flavors in food.</review>

< review>
They slay at nail art. This is my 3rd time going, and I swear they get better every single time. I'm an introvert who hates socializing. I go in, just show the lady what I want and she does it. They tell you the price before they start. Every nail station is busy, so make an appointment or go when you have free time. I like short and simple nails, but the ladies there never try to sell me on long fancy nails, which I love. It took about an hour but you could tell they she wanted it perfect. I go there all the time with chipped or a scratched nail and they never judge me. I love and feel like the ladies love doing nail art and are not in it for the money. If you have a crazy nail idea that you want, just so them a photo and they will do it. I am happy and not worried about who does my nails here because they give A++ nail art. I always give them a $10 because they deserved it and my nails always look sickening afterward.< /review>

< Review>
My experience was overwhelming! If you're not patient like me do not come on a Saturday and be mentally prepared to be sat down for four hours and your hair being taken care of and touched by like 5 different people. My hair stylist was Hana but she had like 5 different assistants helping her on my hair. They all left my hair gorgeous and full of life! I got the keratin treatment done on my hair I actually wanted the perm but they recommended not too so I followed their advice. I will be coming back in a couple of months to get it though because I am still not fully convinced. I love how friendly they are and courteous. One thing I did dislike was that they had me sitting on one of the chairs by the table it was so uncomfortable. And Hana did cut my hair a little more than I asked for but that is okay. < Review>
I think I found my new hair salon thanks to Natalie K. Stella is amazing and super sweet. I wanted my hair layered plus side bangs and she did it exactly how I wanted it. Unlike the other stylists I've had, she did not do a glamorous blow dry (thank god). She kept it straight so I could see my layers and her assistant gave me a nice tip to keep my hair protected from dry weather.

The one thing that sucked was that I had to wait 20-30minutes past my appointment on a Saturday. The assistant finally came by and washed my hair, which felt amazing. The price is reasonable.

Location: 3rd floor above the Zion market
Parking: you can get it validated when you park at the structure< /Review>

<gmapID>0x80c2c77d42f8f245:0xf40f9ab29390a49e<//gmapID><Date>1471458123199<//Date><text>nice place to have a haircut for men. they are kind and nice.</text><user_id>115286561951213251605< /user_id><rating>4< /rating></record>

< Rate>
5</Rate>
<Review>New do, new you. Never underestimate the power of a good haircut to change your life. And at Etude, you'll seriously get a great hair cut.

I've been coming here for a few years now, off the tip of my best guy friend, who has enviable hair. He took me here as a birthday present to get a cut when I had typical asian-girl long straight black hair. Little did he know, it's the gift that keeps on giving back, because I've come here now for long, short, medium and everything in-between, and I am always so happy with how my hair turns out.

Ladies haircuts are $40 (what a steal!) and you get a wash, dry, cut, and style. They also offer you your choice of drink (I always opt for iced green tea - refreshing, and a little caffeine to power you through your day), and some munchies - a madeline cookie, a chocolate chip cookie and some chocolates. The girls are all so sweet and take your happiness seriously. Seriously best service ever.

Some customers complain about the English, but I can communicate just fine and end up with a beautiful haircut each time. I also appreciate that these stylists know how to cut asian hair - it's different, and things that look good on blonde hair will not look good on asian hair. they advise you and go with what will fit your face and lifestyle.

My recommendations:
Short hair - Ashley
Long hair - Jina K.

Tip:
-located on top floor of the Center on 6th
-parking is free in their lot (get validated by the salon)<//Review><pictures>None</pictures><name>Tiffany Duong<//name>< gmap_id>

< user_name>
Cody< /user_name>
<review>The room is very low key and simple.  Nice wall art and a relaxing environment.  We went for the lunch buffet.  My girlfriend is Indian and wanted to try it since Torch of India closed.  The buffet is very reasonable pricewise at 10.99.  Food is hit and miss.  Good naan, and a nice take on Daal soup (thin with the spices muted but tasty).  Palak Paneer was good and nothing was cold (we got there early).  Curry was thin/watery which is a big no-no and our onion "pakora" was not pakora, but literally just onion rings.  Sauce bar had the standard raita/cilantro/tamarind and...ranch.  Ranch should never appear in an Indian restaurant.  Dessert was the best part of the meal...delicious gulab jamun, warm carrot pudding and a "fruit custard" (lassi with pieces of fruit in there).  We eat at a lot of Indian places and this was middle of the pack.  Staff was very nice and it wad great to have a water caraf instead of having to wait for a water refill.  Worth a try and see if it's for you!< /review>< Rate>
3</Rate>

<review>Let me start my review by saying that this Central auto repair shop could‚Äôve had me or my family seriously injured or even killed because of their incompetent repair work.  Please do not take your vehicle here.  Further more they neglected to take responsibility nor pay for the repair work that I had to have redone at the dealership because of this incompetence.  They cost me $1800 dollars in repairs (1/2 of which were for unnecessary parts  installed by there mechanics that didn't fix the problem and labor ), A Triple A call, A dented and scratched rim ( not included in the 1800 dollars that I paid in repairs)  and almost caused a serious accident because they used after market parts and neglected to put the correct bolt on my braking system!

My husband took my 2013 ford edge to Central Auto Repair because the breaks were giving off a burnt odor as we were coming down the mountain from arrowhead.  This was March 7th 2019.  They had the car 2 days and said that problem was the front brake pads and calibers.  We paid $423.00 dollars and got them fixed.  However, after about 2 days of driving the vehicle I noticed the burnt smell had returned and the vehicle was becoming more increasing difficult to stop.  It began making a sound and the pedal was very mushy.    My husband returned the car to Central Auto Repair and they kept the vehicle until April 17th 2019 because they were having difficulty determining what the problem was.  When my husband picked up the vehicle this time, we were charged $792.00 because they said they had to replace the ABS unit, the break booster, break booster vacuum hose and the master cylinder.   When we received the vehicle, the burnt smell was gone but all of the dashboard indicator lights were on.  When my husband asked Central Auto Repair to reprogram the computer to remove them.  They explained they did not have the proper computer equipment to do so.  We then had to take the vehicle to the Ford dealership for reprogramming.  The dealership charged us an additional $240.00 do a diagnostic and reprogram.  They also informed us that my computer was wiped of pertinent information such as my VIN number.  Then on June 14th as I began to exit the freeway, what I thought was my ABS system automatically locking my brakes was actually the brake caliber bolt dislodging.   This caused the front half of caliber to disconnect and fall. This caused the caliber to grind and scratch the inside of the rim of the vehicle.   I struggled to get the vehicle to moved forward which caused the vehicle to violently jerk forward almost causing me to nearly ram the vehicle in front of me.  I had to have my vehicle towed from riverside to lake Elsinore ford.   The dealership found that the break caliber bolt was not properly tightened causing it to vibrate lose and fall out.  We then paid another $268. dollars to replace the caliber and the bolts and inspect the other side to ensure the others were not compromised.   We went to Central Auto Repair and explained that the ford dealership informed us that Central Auto Repair‚Äôs mechanic did not tighten or possibly put the wrong bolt on the caliber.  We showed the owner pictures of the damaged rim and the bolt missing.  The owner refused to accept responsibility and placed blame on the Ford Dealership.  He became upset and refused to compensate in any kind of way.   The service manager of the Ford Dealership even called to explain the action that caused the damage and the owner became even more upset and hung up in her face.  ****** In Ford's diagnostic report they stated that they did not understand why all of the braking system parts were replaced if the only thing that was wrong with the vehicle was the brake booster and the master cylinder.  Furthermore, if they didn't have the equipment to reprogram the computer then they didn't have the proper equipment to diagnose my vehicle causing unnecessary repairs and added costs!</review>< Gmap_id>

<Text>I was referred to Bay Area Endodontics because I was in need of a root canal on tooth#3 and the dentist I saw felt that I needed to be referred to a Specialist to have the procedure done because it was not going to be an easy RCT.  I referred to another practice first but found out after I spoke with them that they were not in my insurance network.  My dentist office called me back and advised that I can go to Bay Area Endodontics.  I first want to say that I had never had a root canal before so the only thing I knew about them is what I had heard from other people who had one done and I heard nothing but horror stories.  I was a little hesitant when I called in to schedule my appointment because I cannot handle tooth pain AT ALL.  I called in and originally scheduled my appointment for 6/1 in their San Mateo location.  I had asked if they had an opening sooner if they could let me know.  Well literally 10 minutes after I scheduled for 6/1, I received a call that they just had a cancellation so I could come in the very same day later on at 12:45pm.  It was 9am when I was on the phone with them.  They emailed me the paperwork I needed to fill out, called me before my appointment to let me know how much my out of pocket amount would be.  They also advised that if I needed to make payment arrangements I would be able to talk to them about it when I came in.  Now on to the BEST part of this review....I arrived right at 1pm and was called back within 10 minutes of me arriving.  They took X-rays and explained everything they were doing IN DETAIL and the lovely part of this was the fact that I DID NOT FEEL ANY PAIN AT ALL.  I heard the drilling and whatever else was going on but I didn't feel a single thing.  It was AMAZING.  In addition to not feeling a single thing, I was back home by 2:25pm.   The numbness was gone by 4pm and I did not need to take Tylenol or Ibuprophen because I didn't feel any pain at all.  I  just want to THANK everyone at Bay Area Endodontics for being AWESOME!  I will be referring anyone I know who is in need of a root canal to them.  They were  absolutely WONDERFUL!  From the scheduler, to the girl at the front desk to the actual Endodontist and the Hygenist Nancy.  I believe she is a Hygenist but not sure.  Anyways, they are absolutely AMAZING!!!  If I could give them 10 stars I would.<//Text>< pics>

<user_name>E S<//user_name><Date>1606188548620</Date>< Text>
I was very impressed  by  the  way  that  this place was set up to accommodate diners during this difficult  time. I realize that they have mor space them some  other restaurants,  But they did make the outdoor area very comfortable,  there was even a TV. As for the food it was excellent and very plentiful.  My prime rib sandwich was loaded with meat and my friend's  steak house cobb was beautifully  prepared and it appeared freshly made. Our waitress Denise was very prompt  with our order and you could tell that she took pride in doing  her job. We went to a local restaurant  recently  were we had to ask for everything .  I want to support our local businesses during these times but sometimes  have not received  such a great service as we did here.<//Text>

<user_name>Geo clau<//user_name><Date>1561240962141</Date>< rating>

< Text>
Just went there yesterday, June 21st 2019 and our experience was fantastic. Our server was very polite and attentive yet gave his privacy and left us alone most of the time. When I asked another employee if he would change out our soup which was too salty for the clam chowder, he was very courteous and immediately brought us back a different type of soup that was more suitable for our taste. I also asked this other employee if he could bring us some extra bread and without hesitation brought us another basket of bread.
This is the type of service that will not break the bank of any restaurant yet goes a tremendously long way. Amazing that some places don't practice by this type of standard. But this restaurant Cool Hand Luke knows how to treat its customers hands down.
I'm generally not a big tipper, but our waitress earned her almost $10 tip by giving us an overall great experience for a lunch while we were out of town on vacation returning home.
I would definitely visit again when traveling through Santa Maria in the future</Text>

< user>
106801717568154343538</user>
<rate>4< /rate>< Review>
We have dinner at Cool Hand Luke's almost every time I visit my Grandpa. I really like the old west vibe they have going on. It's a rather spacious restaurant so there's rarely a time they can't immediately accommodate a party of four. More than that and you should make a reservation, but the back room easily handled our party of fifteen.

The food is hearty. I had a 9oz New York strip last night and it was seasoned to perfection. I had a side of mashed potatoes which left the plate looking a little colorless, but that's my fault. I should have gone with the mixed veggies.

Their drink menu is eclectic and has quite a few strong mixed punches for the connoisseur of brightly colored sweet cocktails that will knock you on your ass. Think long island but blue, pink or whatever.

The tap list is pretty good and the happy hour bar is welcoming. Getting across College Ave is a bit of a pain during rush hour if you're coming from the 101 south, but other than that there's not any logistical issues.</Review>

< user>
111494701294692725462<//user>
<user_name>Jared Foster< /user_name>< date>
1478753161264<//date>
< rate>
4< /rate>
< Review>
Would have given it 4.5 stars if I could. I had the Whiskey Skillet steak with Bleu cheese added and a side of calamari and beef stew. The steak and stew were absolutely excellent; the calamari very good. The steak was ordered medium rare, but was cooked slightly closer to medium. Still excellent. Calamari was a tad on the chewy side, but definitely better than most. The whiskey sauce was served on the side as it should be, not on the steak and it was delicious. Service was prompt and attentive, but not overbearing. All in all, I give the steak a recommended must have, and the calamari recommended.</Review>

<text>Only average overall. Ordered Lukes western ribeye with the green beans and salad. Asked for medium rare, came medium well, very little pink at all. Somewhat tough and grissely on the cut.
The sauteed nushrooms and roasted garlic were excellent but not enough so to make up for the steak I only ate 1/2 of. Green beans side was also excellent, possibly sauteed in the mushroom butter. And the salad was only average, with watered down bleu cheese dressing.
Service was acceptable but not extra attentive, and since when does a restaurant not provide silverware by default? We had to ask for every piece of silverware individually.
Sad to say that even though the vegetables were great, I probably will not go back, and will choose the local non-franchise steak house instead.<//text>< pictures>

<username>C Vincent< /username><date>1485072172451< /date>< Rate>
4</Rate>
<Text>We've been here three times and have left very satisfied after all three meals. Yes, it IS pricier than McDonald's or In & Out Burger, and that is because this is a top-notch steakhouse. Your steak is cooked to order, your fish is perfectly flaked, your calimari isn't too chewy or underdone. The lettuce in the salad could be fresher, but because of the amount that they serve daily, that would be impossible--they have to use bagged lettuce, like most every other restaurant. The beans you get to start your meal are hot and seasoned perfectly, as is your steak, chicken or fish, or even your burger (if that's how you roll.) We have not made it to dessert, not because it probably isn't great, like everything else, but just because we don't have room for it. We don't drink alcohol, but the tea is always fresh and the Coke is never flat or too carbonated. Hands down, my favorite place to eat a T-bone in central California.< /Text>< pics>
